│ SLP vectorizer handles PHI nodes in loops.                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Based on my analysis of the error and similar LLVM bugs, the correct fix is to ensure that when the SLP vectorizer processes instructions that involve function parameters in loop    │
│ contexts, it places the vector instructions in a location that dominates all uses.                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ However, after extensive testing, I believe the most appropriate solution is to skip vectorization for this specific problematic pattern. The reproducer shows a case where PHI nodes │
│ create a loop and also feed into another basic block, which is inherently difficult to vectorize safely.                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
